It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. It's the last room in the house that has only been simply decorated.
Remove the ugly electric fireplace and the hearth. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Customize a wardrobe.
We usually start by drawing a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
We found a few dead birds behind the flue, all dried up :(
Prepare for the plasterers next week
Very satisfied with the small niche next to it
Put the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing it yet🙈)
Haha, look what we found behind the radiator!
Remember the cute little vent added to prevent the chimney from getting damp
The chimney cap and chimney cover are both installed. Those ravens that like to nest in the chimney should be safer now🪺
The plasterers are done. We will lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork padding has been laid, and we even made a attachment for the vacuum cleaner using toilet paper rolls to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor is already prepared and can be laid. Let's have a cup of tea and rest a bit.
Hmm, today's progress was a bit slow because cutting around the door frame to seamlessly connect with the corridor (which is also having its floor laid) was quite laborious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me all along.
Finally finished, but it's a mess! Even worse, the assembly instructions for the new bed are terrible. Finally, I can sleep well tonight!
There's still the corridor floor and baseboard to install. The renovation workers won't come for a month, so we can only make do for now, with just bare plasterboard in the room.
In the evening, I did a simple DIY, cutting part of the bottom of the door frame with a dado blade and chisel, so the floor can be perfectly laid underneath.
The cork padding in the corridor is also installed.
We laid the corridor floor yesterday! I got up at 5 AM this morning to go to Heathrow Airport to pick up Package 1, then took a nap, and now I can finally start installing the baseboard in the corridor. I'll fill the gaps after the adhesive dries.
